  "response": "Saudi Arabia is known for its strict interpretation of Islamic law and does not officially recognize atheism. Public expression of atheistic views can lead to severe legal consequences, including imprisonment or harsher penalties. \n\nWhile there may indeed be individuals in Saudi Arabia who hold atheistic beliefs, they often do not publicly share their views due to the risk of persecution. Informally, some might find ways to express their doubts privately or engage in discussions in hidden settings, but open atheism is not tolerated. \n\nThe situation can be complex, as some individuals may identify as cultural Muslims or may be skeptical of religious practices while still outwardly conforming to societal norms due to the potential repercussions.",
